| # | Finding | Severity | Exploitability | Impact |
|---|---------|----------|----------------|--------|
| 1 | Non-constant-time signature comparison (timing oracle) | **High** | Moderate (requires many requests, network precision) | Full auth bypass possible over time |
| 2 | AWS Signature V2 (HMAC-SHA1) accepted without restriction | **High** | Low–Moderate (requires downgrade or legacy client) | Weaker algorithm; body substitution possible |
| 3 | 15-minute replay attack window, no nonce tracking | **Medium** | Low (requires request interception) | Captured signed requests replayable |
| 4 | Unsigned payload accepted by default | **Medium** | Moderate (requires MITM position) | Body integrity not guaranteed on write ops |
| 5 | Signing-key chain and signatures emitted to debug logs | **Low** | Low (requires log access) | Key material / signature exposure |

